						<summary>

						<p>Slab near the Hanuman temple opposite the Venkateśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1693 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that the God Sañjīva-Hanumantadēva was installed at Siravāra by Gururāya, the son of Venkappa of Jamadagni-gōtra and hailing from Nāmalagāvi.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1615, Śrīmukha, Chaitra, śu. 1, Monday corresponding to 1693 A.D., March 27. </p>						

						</summary>
